text: Fischbach () is a commune and village in central Luxembourg. It is part of the canton of Mersch, which is part of the district of Luxembourg. , the village of Fischbach, which lies in the centre of the commune, had a population of 178. Other towns within the commune include Angelsberg and Schoos. Fischbach is the site of Fischbach Castle, one of the private residences of the Grand Ducal family. ==See also== *List of villages in Luxembourg ==References== ==External links== * Category:Communes in Mersch (canton) Category:Villages in Luxembourg
